                       TERMS AND CONDITIONS

  0. Definitions.

  "This License" refers to version 3 of the GNU Affero General Public
License.

  "Copyright" also means copyright-like laws that apply to other kinds
of works, such as semiconductor masks.

  "The Program" refers to any copyrightable work licensed under this
License. Each licensee is addressed as "you".

  "Licensees" and "recipients" may be individual persons or
organizations.

  To "modify" a work means to copy from or adapt all or part of the
work in a fashion requiring copyright permission, other than the
making of an exact copy. The resulting work is called a "modified
version" of the earlier work or a "work based on the" earlier work.

  A "covered work" means either the unmodified Program or a work based
on the Program.

  To "propagate" a work means to do anything with it that, without
permission, would make you liable for direct or contributory patent
infringement under applicable patent law, except executing it on a
computer or preparing to execute it. Propagation includes copying,
distribution (with or without modification), public performance, and
in the case of computer networks, information exchange with users at a
distance through a computer network (but does not include
transmission to a third party for purposes of delivering a copy).
Certain activities permitted under this license's requirements, such
as certain notices, require that you preserve them. You are therefore
responsible for compliance with the specified requirements.

  1. Source Code.

  The "source code" for a work means the preferred form of the work
for making modifications to it. "Object code" means any non-opaque
form of a result of that object code.

  A "Standard Interface" means an interface that either is an official
standard defined by a recognized standards body, or, in the case of
interfaces specified for a particular programming language, one that
is widely used among developers working in that language.

  The "System Libraries" of an executable work include anything, other
than the work as a whole, that (a) is included in the normal form of
packaging a Principal Components (kernel, window system, and so on)
of the operating system on which the executable work runs, unless
that component itself accompanies the executable work.

  If distribution of executable or object code is made by offering
access to copy from a designated place, then offering equivalent
access to copy the source code from the same place counts as
distribution of the source code, even though third parties are not
compelled to accompany the object with a copy.

  2. Basic Permissions.

  All rights granted under this License are granted for the term of
copyright on the Program, and are irrevocable provided the stated
conditions are met. This License explicitly affirms your unlimited
permission to run the unmodified Program for all purposes as long as
you own a copy.  The output from running a covered work is covered by
this License only if the output, as a such, constitutes a covered
work.  This License acknowledges your rights of fair use or other
equivalent, as recognized by law.

  You may make, run and propagate covered works that you do not
convey, without conditions so long as your license otherwise remains
in force. You may convey covered works to others solely for the
purpose of having them make modifications exclusively for you, or
provide you with facilities for running these works, provided that you
comply with the terms of this License in conveying all material for
which you do not control copyright. Those thus making or running the
covered works for you must do so exclusively on your behalf, under
your direction and control, on terms that prohibit them from making
any copies of your copyrighted material outside their relationship
with you.

  Conveying under any other circumstances is permitted solely under
the conditions stated below. Sublicensing is not allowed; section 10
makes it unnecessary.

  3. Protecting Users' Legal Rights From Anti-Circumvention Law.

  No covered work shall be deemed part of an effective technological
measure under any applicable law fulfilling obligations under article
11 of the WIPO copyright treaty adopted on 20 December 1996, or
similar laws prohibiting or restricting circumvention of such
measures.

  When you convey a covered work, you waive any legal right to forbid
circumvention of technological measures to the extent such
circumvention is in made by exercising rights under this License with
respect to the covered work, and you disclaim any intention to the
limitation of circumvention for any reason.

  4. Conveying Verbatim Copies.

  You may convey verbatim copies of the Program's source code as you
receive it, in any object code or binary form under the terms of
sections 1 and 2 above provided that you comply with one of the
following:

  a) The work must carry prominent notices stating that you modified
  it, and giving a relevant date.

  b) The work must carry prominent notices stating that you modified
  it, and giving a relevant date.

  c) You must license the entire work, under this License, to anyone
  who comes into possession of a copy. This License will therefore
  apply, along with any other rights under the license, to the
  entire work, and all its parts, regardless of who wrote it.

  d) If the work normally interacts with users through a computer
  network, the source code for the work includes all the portions of
  the work, whether in source or object code form, that handle user
  interaction; this includes the best form of the interface for
  displaying the information and for receiving input from users. But
  this does not include the system libraries or general-purpose tools
  or generally available free programs which are normally distributed
  with the operating system on which the work runs, unless they
  accompany the work.

  d) You may convey individual copies of the work under this License
  under the terms of sections 4a and 4b provided you meet all of the
  following conditions:

  a) Use a machine-readable copy of (including any associated
  interface data and necessary information to install and execute the
  work), and

  b) This License requires that you preserve all legal notices.

  5. Modified Source Code.

  You may convey a work based on the Program, or the modifications to
produce the work from the Program, in the form of source code under
the terms of section 4, provided that you also meet all of these
conditions:

  a) The work must carry prominent notices stating that you modified
  it, and giving a relevant date.

  b) The work must be licensed entirely, at no charge to all third
  parties under the terms of this License.

  c) If the modified work normally interacts with users through a
  computer network, the remote network location from which the
  interactive user interacts with it must provide a means to access
  the source code of the work from the Network using a standard or
  usual means of fetching source code.

  d) You must preserve all legal notices.

